shared_text:
Georgetown Charter Academy
August 6 at 9:18 PM 路

We will host an open house on August 20th from 5 pm to 7 pm. This will not be a come and go event as it has been in the past. Each student will be assigned a certain time frame (30 min.) during which they have to come to campus. This will help us to avoid large crowds at once. Invitations, with the time for your family, will be send out next week. The nutrition department will be in attendance to accept application for free and reduced lunches. If your child rides the bus make sure to meet with the transportation department so they can give you the location, time for the departure and arrival time. After school care will be set up so you can sign up your child. We have worked hard all summer and finished some amazing restoration to the campus. We can't wait to show it off to you. GCA has been granted the official STEAM (Science Technology Engineering Art Math) designation. We are very excited for this coming year and will take it one day at a time. These are trying times for all of us, but we are a team and can do anything we put our minds to. GO ROADRUNNERS!!!

shared_text:
Zaida Kopriva is with Tammy Hobdy Knox.
May 27 at 9:10 AM 路

Cades School awards ceremony at Temple Charter Academy School. This year of Kinder was so full of up and downs with Cades health. We never knew he would have gotten so sick throughout school. But through it all we had an amazing loving teacher Tammy Hobdy Knox who loved him with all her heart and kept encouraging him and teaching him the best that she could since he missed lots of school.
Some how she kept him on task and he grew so much this first year of school. He is so smart and knows so much and I thank the school system for that and his teacher.

I recommend this school to anyone who may need that smaller school environment for their child. It has been a beyond what I expected kindergarten year for Cade. We will miss all the sweet staff that are part of this school. Big hugs and we will have to come visit from time to time. Cade is now ready for Kinder in Troy!! わ we will miss you so much Mrs. Knox! And we will never forget all the love you put into our son Cade!!  we are so proud of our little baby boy!! Lots of awards for our smarty pants!!

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefits Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

shared_text:
ESC Region 12 was live.
May 13 at 7:00 PM 路

Even when life is interrupted by a global pandemic, life is still happening. We still have homes to run, we still have to find things we need. We're trying to keep our families together, yet safely apart and we're trying to keep our kids learning when their school buildings stand silent. In this brief conversation, we'll explore what keeps us together as parents and educators and discuss what we have to guard against from ripping us apart. We're not necessarily experiencing it like everyone else. But one thing is for certain; we're all experiencing it. We're living through the same storm, but experiencing it in a different boat.

post_text:
Congratulations to Georgetown Charter Academy for earning 3rd place at Central Texas District Championship Meet!
On Saturday, October 26th, GCA middle school students competed in the Texas Charter Schools Academic and Athletic League (TCSAAL), Central Texas District Championships in San Antonio. GCA middle school boys won the 3rd place trophy in the Secondary Team Division. The team was lead by 5th grader Christian Medina, who ran the 2 mile course in 17:01. This is the first year Georgetown Charter Academy has participated in TCSAAL. Georgetown Charter Academy was joined by two of its sister schools, Cove Charter Academy and Cedar Park Charter Academy for the meet. Both schools had high school athletes placed in the top 10 for the Junior Varsity division.

post_text:
It is that time of year again we have been hard at work this year preparing for you to come back. District-wide we have been training, cleaning and updating just for you to come back. We started the year last Tuesday with our 20th Anniversary Celebration at Temple Charter Academy
for a district-wide convocation. The Transportation Department has been hard at work cleaning and working on buses. Meanwhile the Child Nutrition Department had their 2nd annual back to school training. Can't wait to see everyone on August 19th!!!

post_text:
IF THE WEATHER IS BAD...?

Occasionally, weather forces a delay in the school start time or the entire day of classes has to be postponed. If the weather requires either a delay in start time or a postponement for the day, the announcement is made through our SchoolMessenger庐 program. SchoolMessenger庐 allows us to send a phone announcement to all phone numbers we have on record, an email to the parent's email address on record, and a text message to the cell phone on record.

Sign up for a SchoolMessenger庐 account here: https://accounts.relianceco.com/cm/#register

Update contact information for an existing SchoolMessenger庐 account here: https://accounts.relianceco.com/cm/#login

Learn more about SchoolMessenger庐 here: http://schoolmessenger.com/

It is very important that parents help all campuses maintain up to date records. If any part of the parent's contact information changes, the parent should let the school office know as soon as possible.

School delays or cancellations are also posted on this website no later than 5:30 the morning of the delay or cancellation.

post_text:
NOTICE OF CALENDAR REVISION

Priority Charter Schools has made a small revision to the 2013-2014 school calendar. Due to an increased need by a number of our students, there will be Dyslexia Therapy training for all staff on January 3, 2014. Plans had called for a Teacher Inservice day on January 3 and now that inservice training has been moved to January 6, 2014. Therefore, PCS students at all campuses will return to school on January 7. The last day of the school year for students will be June 4. Teachers will complete their yearly duties on June 5 and 6.

View the revised calendar here: http://www.prioritycharter.org/School-Calendar_ep_66.html.
